<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870527-0015 </DOCNO><HL> Stewart Sandwiches StakeOf 5.42% Held by Investors</HL><DD> 05/27/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> STEWTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   A group including Baupost Group Inc., a Cambridge, Mass.-based investment advisory firm, said it holds a 5.42% stake in Stewart Sandwiches Inc.    In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, the group said it holds 99,500 shares in the Norfolk, Va., maker of prepackaged sandwiches, including 57,000 shares purchased from March 27 to Friday for $1.98 to $2.05 each.    According to the filing, the group holds its Stewart Sandwiches shares for investment purposes and may buy or sell additional shares depending on market conditions and other factors.    In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, Stewart Sandwiches closed at $2.125, up 21.875 cents. </TEXT></DOC>